hat sample processing is vital in obtaining high-performance materials.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>Nanocomposite half-Heuslers have been shown to have promising energy conversion efficiencies and are promising candidates for use in thermoelectric devices. We are currently trying to attract funding to increase the technological readiness of these materials.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>A4C6A1CC-88E4-477A-B537-0B1DE1A0530F</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>545cab32b99489.69039813</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Energy</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>52E0DE91-4D4B-4CA4-BB3E-F97DAA3290EC</gtr:id><gtr:title>Enhanced thermoelectric performance in TiNiSn-based half-Heuslers.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Chemical communications (Cambridge, England)</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/47ba22979d2df239e34c0795968f65f1"><gtr:id>47ba22979d2df239e34c0795968f65f1</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Downie RA</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2013-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>1359-7345</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>544e0d91cfead2.91424807</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>0EDD935F-EFBC-4EB9-B012-504560A3C74F</gtr:id><gtr:title>Metal Distributions, Efficient n-Type Doping, and Evidence for in-Gap States in TiNiM
 
